To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Hello, 
Can you please authenticate the following information and provide the following records:
Department of Homeland Security > Federal Emergency Management Agency > Student Identification Number: 0000866833

Also please provide a list of certificated held by this ID number and the name attached to this ID Number.


This request is not being made for commercial purposes.

There should be no fees associated with this request but in the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would fulfill my request and attach an invoice. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment of a written letter.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Mason C. Turner
TurnerMason@gmail.com

title: Vehicle Pursuit Dashcam video and body camera (Forest Park Police Department)

communications.subject: Georgia Open Records Act Request: Vehicle Pursuit Dashcam video and body camera (Forest Park Police Department)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Georgia Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Copies of dashcam and or bodycam video of police pursuits from 01/02/2021 to 01/02/2024.  I would like vehicle and foot pursuits.  Please include an abbreviated processing note for each video

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Michael Faulkner
